heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 10th for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 10.1mm per hour sustained for 13.7 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 9.21mm.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.
